# rust-r2026t Workspace Convention

The **rust-2026-Trahloc Microcrate Convention (r2026t)** is a strict layout, naming, and configuration standard. Supersedes r2025t — layout invariants unchanged; r2026t adds centralized dep/lint config and toolchain pinning.

## The Uniqueness Invariant

> For every crate directory `X/`, the root module is `X.rs` (flattened) or `src/X.rs` (binary only).

**Banned**: `mod.rs` (strictly forbidden everywhere) · `lib.rs`/`main.rs` as logic containers (max 5 lines as tooling redirects only).

Never name a crate `core` — shadows `std::core`. Use `common`, `shared`, or `kernel`.

## Workspace Structure

```
<root>/
├── Cargo.toml              # workspace root
├── rust-toolchain.toml     # toolchain pin (r2026t)
├── .cargo/config.toml      # linker + sccache
├── bin/                    # binary (uses src/)
├── lib/                    # shared microcrates (no src/)
├── tests/                  # integration test crate
└── command/                # optional: CLI verb crates
```

## Workspace Cargo.toml (canonical template)

```toml
[workspace]
members = ["bin", "lib/*", "tests"]
resolver = "2"

[workspace.dependencies]           # centralized dep versions (r2026t)
serde = { version = "1", features = ["derive"] }
serde_json = "1"
tracing = "0.1"

[workspace.lints.rust]             # workspace-wide lint policy (r2026t)
unused_imports = "deny"
dead_code = "deny"
unused_variables = "deny"

[workspace.lints.clippy]
all = "warn"

[profile.dev]
opt-level = 0
debug = true
incremental = true

[profile.dev.package."*"]
opt-level = 2
```

## Member Crate Cargo.toml (template)

```toml
[package]
name = "myapp-lib-common"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2024"
publish = false              # all internal crates (r2026t)

[lib]
name = "myapp_lib_common"
path = "common.rs"           # explicit path; no src/

[lints]
workspace = true             # inherit [workspace.lints] (r2026t)

[dependencies]
serde = { workspace = true } # inherit version from workspace
myapp-lib-other = { path = "../other" }  # path deps stay per-crate
```

## rust-toolchain.toml

```toml
[toolchain]
channel = "stable"
components = ["rustfmt", "clippy", "rust-src"]
```

## Crate Naming

`<project>-<kind>-<tld>` — `<kind>` is `bin`, `lib`, `tests`, or `command`.

| Dir | Package | Lib/Bin Name |
|---|---|---|
| `bin/` | `myapp-bin` | binary `myapp` |
| `lib/common/` | `myapp-lib-common` | `myapp_lib_common` |
| `tests/` | `myapp-tests` | `myapp_tests` |

## Feature Flag Strategy

Features flow **downward binary → libs. Never upward.**

```toml
[features]
default = ["install"]
install = ["myapp-command-install"]
verbose-logging = ["myapp-lib-common/logging"]  # propagated

[dependencies]
myapp-command-install = { path = "../command/install", optional = true }
```

## Microcrate Splitting Criteria

Split only when a threshold is met — NOT by line count:

| # | Criterion |
|---|---|
| 1 | Type Proliferation: 3+ non-trivial public types/traits |
| 2 | Dependency Isolation: heavy dep nothing else needs |
| 3 | Test Divergence: materially different fixtures/setup |
| 4 | Independent Versioning: separate semver/feature-gating |
| 5 | Collaboration Boundary: two devs/agents work simultaneously |

**Goal**: Change one file → rebuild one crate → tests in < 2s.
**Path**: Module → Nested Microcrate → `lib/<name>/` (promoted library)

## Testing

**Unit tests**: In-file `#[cfg(test)] mod tests { ... }`. Never in separate files.

**Integration tests**: Workspace crate `tests/` (NOT bare Cargo test folder):

```toml
# tests/Cargo.toml
[package]
name = "myapp-tests"
edition = "2024"
publish = false

[lints]
workspace = true

[[test]]
name = "integration"
path = "integration.rs"
```

```bash
cargo test -p myapp-lib-common   # unit tests
cargo test -p myapp-tests        # integration tests
cargo test --workspace           # everything
```

## Tooling

```toml
# .cargo/config.toml
[target.x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu]
linker = "clang"
rustflags = ["-C", "link-arg=-fuse-ld=mold"]

[build]
rustc-wrapper = "sccache"
```

```bash
cargo watch -x check                        # continuous type checking
cargo watch -x "test -p myapp-lib-common"   # test on save
```

## External Repositories

Cloned third-party repositories (for reference, patching, or upstream PRs) MUST be placed in the `/external/` directory.

The standard `.gitignore` ensures that the massive histories and files of these third-party repos do not pollute the workspace's version control. However, we explicitly track ALL `README.md` files within `external/` as breadcrumbs. The root `external/README.md` acts as an index of what repos we have and why, and the individual `external/<repo>/README.md` files are the original upstream readmes kept to provide context on the clone.

## r2026t vs r2025t Delta

| Area | r2025t | r2026t |
|---|---|---|
| Dep versions | per-crate only | `[workspace.dependencies]` + `{ workspace = true }` |
| Lint config | `.cargo/config.toml` rustflags | `[workspace.lints]` + `[lints] workspace = true` |
| Toolchain | unspecified | `rust-toolchain.toml` |
| `publish = false` | `tests/` only | all internal crates |
| Edition | mixed 2021/2024 | 2024 everywhere |
| Layout | ✓ | unchanged |
